<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<organisationUsers>
  <!--
    Live user records should be stored on Render persistent disk at /data/users.xml.

    For personal data protection, do not store live full names and email addresses
    in plaintext in GitHub.

    The updated server.js encrypts plaintext <name> and <email> into:
      <encryptedName>...</encryptedName>
      <encryptedEmail>...</encryptedEmail>

    using AES-256-GCM and the PERSONAL_DATA_KEY Render environment variable.

    Recommended GitHub template:
      Keep this file empty or use it only as a non-live template.

    To onboard approved users safely:
      1. Prepare approved users in a local/private copy of users.xml using plaintext
         <name> and <email> only in a secure environment.
      2. Deploy with PERSONAL_DATA_KEY set.
      3. Copy/import that file to Render persistent disk.
      4. The server will migrate plaintext name/email to encryptedName/encryptedEmail
         in the live /data/users.xml file.
      5. Do not commit live /data/users.xml back to GitHub.
  -->
</organisationUsers>
